<table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width="95%"><TR><td bgcolor="#ffffff"><TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="100%"><TR bgcolor="#000080"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#ffffff" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#DEDFDF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Steffin</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Is it possible to mez FGs in Sol B?  If so what spell is needed?  I am level 51.<P>Steffin Soulcharmer</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#F7F7F7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Hika</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Nope.<P>Your recourse is root, charm, or both.<P>-- Hika<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#DEDFDF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Mesphaet</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Not to sound rude, but you are level 51 and didn't know you can't Mez/stun giants?<P>/shrug<P></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#F7F7F7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Trinket</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Root is usually not an option since FGs tend to summon 8-) Charm is your friend 8-) They get very easy when you get Boltrans at 53. Fast recast and low aggro is really really nice espectially for FGs.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#DEDFDF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Steffin</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Wow Mesphaet!  You seem like a pretty nice fellow.  As a matter of fact, enchanters used to be able to mez giants with Dazzle.  Was nerfed.  Another enchanter said it was still possible.  I didn't think it was but was not totally sure.  Therefore, I came to this board.  Isn't that what this board was for?  <P>BTW, I never said anything about stuns.  Thank you for your lack of constructive input. <P>Steffin Soulcharmer<BR>Innoruuk Server </FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#F7F7F7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Hika</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial"> <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR>Originally posted by Trinket:<BR><B>Root is usually not an option since FGs tend to summon </B><HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>Root is a perfect option for summoning mobs.  A rooted NPC does NOT summon.  <P>This is because summoning was originally implemented as anti-exploit code as follows:<P>if an NPC can legally move, but cannot reach its hated target, it will summon the target.<P>A rooted NPC cannot legally move, and therefore will not summon.<P>Watch closely the next time you fight level 51+ NPCs that summon.  Root the one being fought, then note that the same tick you see "Your Root spell has worn off", the NPC will start summoning again.<P><BR>Root is absolutely perfect for handling unmezzable NPCs of any level, provided they aren't immune to magic in the first place.<P>-- Hika<P><BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#DEDFDF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Trinket</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Rooted FGs summon. They do 8-) </FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#F7F7F7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Hika</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial"> <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR>Originally posted by Trinket:<BR><B>Rooted FGs summon. They do 8-) </B><HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>See, when I root giants (or any other 51+ NPC), they don't summon, not until the milisecond root breaks (usually coincided with someone's weapon proccing or an ice comet).<P>-- Hika<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#DEDFDF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Trinket</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Dunno, i can agree to disagree 8-)<P>I've done tranix/skarlon about 20 times easy with my group and i gave up trynig the root strategy because i would root, try to run back to the group battle, which would just result in me getting summoned back all the time. Since their melee range is so long, i suppose it IS possible they were rooted and summoneing me as i was running away, still in melee range and thus attackable. If you rooted one from a distance maybe that is the deciding factor.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#F7F7F7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Llorian</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Since my higher level character is a Shaman ( and thus i have to root/park when there is no enchanter), this is what i have found :<P>When a summoning class mob is NOT damaged in any way, and rooted (not druid root since this does damage), they dont summon. If they are damaged at ALL ( ie damage shields, Melee, DD, Dot Etc) they will summon if they cant whack someone in melee range.<P>So..<P>If your root parking a mob as a form of crowd control, make sure your pullers dont have on any form of DS, as then all the mobs will be damaged (and then start summoning you.<P>You can also root the target your tank is on (gonna piss off your snarer tho) to keep the mob from summoning YOU, the fragile enchanter, regardless of how much hate it has.  If a mob is rooted, it effectively hates whoever is closest to it, untill the root breaks anyway.  As long as you have a mob rooted, and melee types are smashing it, it wont summon.<P>I have never seen a root stick to a dragon / god type mob so i dont know about them =)<P>Arodan Plainswalker<BR>55 Luminary<P>Llorian Plainswalker <BR>37 Enchanter<P>Lanys<P></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#DEDFDF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Llorian</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">GAH !<P>Im sorry-- i was flipping thru this section and didnt realize how old this post was  ..<P>/e bonks Llorian on the head !<P></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#F7F7F7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Alandrel</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I thought this post sounded familiar  <IMG SRC="http://forums.castersrealm.com/eq/wink.gif"> Oh well. Something to read on a slow day at work.<P>------------------<BR>Alandrel Mesmer</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#DEDFDF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">canitiel</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">hmmmm, or maby a good thing to read on a day off of work with no everquest to keep me ocupied! YIPPPIE!!</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#F7F7F7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Llarn</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Well, it may be old but Hika is wrong... as Llorian says, if a mob has been damaged it can summon, rooted or not. I get summoned by rooted golems in Hole and Juggs in OS. Then I have to scream for a tank to start beating on it to get it off me.<P>------------------<BR>Llarn &lt;Prophecy&gt;<BR>L55 Enchanter, Bertoxxulous</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#DEDFDF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Branar</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Or just back up so that someone else is standing closer to it than you...Rooted mobs move closer targets to the top of their hate lists.<P>Better them than you, right?  <IMG SRC="http://forums.castersrealm.com/eq/wink.gif"><P>------------------<BR>Branar Shmanar<BR>*Forged Souls*<BR>55 enchanter<BR>The Seventh Hammer</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE></td></tr></table> 
